––– comment –––
Test Cluster Commands with effective replication user option.
Spec: https://github.com/manticoresoftware/manticoresearch/blob/wip_auth/src/auth/spec.md
Issue: https://github.com/manticoresoftware/manticoresearch/issues/2983
Admin credentials: admin / adminpass (bootstrap via auth.json)

Per spec:
- CREATE/JOIN CLUSTER support user option as "'<username>' AS user"
- DELETE CLUSTER and ALTER CLUSTER ADD/DROP/UPDATE nodes do not support statement user option
- Effective user must have REPLICATION permission
- ALTER CLUSTER supports "UPDATE user '<username>'"
––– comment –––
––– block: ../base/start-searchd-with-auth –––
––– comment –––
––– Setup: create users with different permissions –––
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -E -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE USER 'repluser' IDENTIFIED BY 'repluser1234';"
––– output –––
*************************** 1. row ***************************
       token: #!/[0-9a-f]{64}/!#
    username: repluser
generated_at: #!/([0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2} [0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}|[A-Z][a-z]{2} [A-Z][a-z]{2} [ 0-9][0-9] [0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}\.[0-9]{3} [0-9]{4})/!#
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "GRANT replication ON * TO 'repluser';"
––– output –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -E -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE USER 'repluser2' IDENTIFIED BY 'repluser2234';"
––– output –––
*************************** 1. row ***************************
       token: #!/[0-9a-f]{64}/!#
    username: repluser2
generated_at: #!/([0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2} [0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}|[A-Z][a-z]{2} [A-Z][a-z]{2} [ 0-9][0-9] [0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}\.[0-9]{3} [0-9]{4})/!#
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "GRANT replication ON * TO 'repluser2';"
––– output –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -E -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE USER 'norepluser' IDENTIFIED BY 'norepluser1';"
––– output –––
*************************** 1. row ***************************
       token: #!/[0-9a-f]{64}/!#
    username: norepluser
generated_at: #!/([0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2} [0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}|[A-Z][a-z]{2} [A-Z][a-z]{2} [ 0-9][0-9] [0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}:[0-9]{2}\.[0-9]{3} [0-9]{4})/!#
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "GRANT read ON * TO 'norepluser';"
––– output –––
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.1 CREATE CLUSTER with explicit effective user: valid replication user –––
EXPECTED: Command accepted
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE CLUSTER mycluster 'repluser' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.2 CREATE CLUSTER with explicit effective user: no replication permission –––
EXPECTED: Error - user lacks replication permission
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE CLUSTER badcluster 'norepluser' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'norepluser'
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.3 CREATE CLUSTER with explicit effective user: unknown user (permission denied) –––
EXPECTED: Error - user lacks replication permission
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE CLUSTER fakecluster 'nonexistent' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'nonexistent'
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.4 ALTER CLUSTER UPDATE user: change assigned user –––
EXPECTED: Command accepted for valid user
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "ALTER CLUSTER mycluster UPDATE user 'repluser2';" 2>&1
––– output –––
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.5 JOIN CLUSTER with explicit effective user: no replication permission –––
EXPECTED: Error - user lacks replication permission
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "JOIN CLUSTER testcluster AT '127.0.0.1:9312' 'norepluser' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'norepluser'
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.6 DELETE CLUSTER with explicit user option is rejected (unsupported syntax) –––
EXPECTED: Syntax error
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "DELETE CLUSTER mycluster 'norepluser' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
#!/ERROR 1064 \(42000\) at line 1: P03: syntax error.*!#
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.7 ALTER CLUSTER ADD with explicit user option is rejected (unsupported syntax) –––
EXPECTED: Syntax error
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "ALTER CLUSTER mycluster ADD testtable 'norepluser' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
#!/ERROR 1064 \(42000\) at line 1: P03: syntax error.*!#
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.8 ALTER CLUSTER DROP with explicit user option is rejected (unsupported syntax) –––
EXPECTED: Syntax error
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "ALTER CLUSTER mycluster DROP testtable 'norepluser' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
#!/ERROR 1064 \(42000\) at line 1: P03: syntax error.*!#
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.9 ALTER CLUSTER UPDATE nodes with explicit user option is rejected (unsupported syntax) –––
EXPECTED: Syntax error
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "ALTER CLUSTER mycluster UPDATE nodes 'norepluser' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
#!/ERROR 1064 \(42000\) at line 1: P03: syntax error.*!#
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.10 ALTER CLUSTER UPDATE '<username>' AS user is rejected (unsupported syntax) –––
EXPECTED: Syntax error
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "ALTER CLUSTER mycluster UPDATE 'repluser' AS user;" 2>&1
––– output –––
#!/ERROR 1064 \(42000\) at line 1: P03: syntax error.*!#
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.11 Persisted cluster user is used for ALTER UPDATE nodes (not session user) –––
EXPECTED: After revoking repluser2 replication, ALTER UPDATE nodes fails for repluser2
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "REVOKE replication ON * FROM 'repluser2';"
––– output –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "ALTER CLUSTER mycluster UPDATE nodes;" 2>&1
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'repluser2'
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.12 Persisted cluster user is used for ALTER ADD (not session user) –––
EXPECTED: Fails for repluser2 before operation-specific checks
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "ALTER CLUSTER mycluster ADD testtable;" 2>&1
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'repluser2'
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.13 Persisted cluster user is used for ALTER DROP (not session user) –––
EXPECTED: Fails for repluser2 before operation-specific checks
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "ALTER CLUSTER mycluster DROP testtable;" 2>&1
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'repluser2'
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.14 Persisted cluster user is used for DELETE CLUSTER (not session user) –––
EXPECTED: Fails for repluser2
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "DELETE CLUSTER mycluster;" 2>&1
––– output –––
ERROR 1064 (42000) at line 1: Permission denied for user 'repluser2'
––– comment –––
––– 8.2.15 Cleanup: restore repluser2 replication permission –––
EXPECTED: Command accepted
––– comment –––
––– input –––
MYSQL_PWD=adminpass mysql -uadmin -h0 -P9306 -e "GRANT replication ON * TO 'repluser2';"
